# CoAgent4U — Codebase Walkthrough

> **AI-powered collaborative scheduling platform** built as a **Java 21 / Spring Boot 3.4 modular monolith** using **hexagonal architecture**.

---

## What Is CoAgent4U?

CoAgent4U is a **Personal Agent Coordination Platform** — not a chatbot. It assigns each user a personal AI agent that can:

1. **Manage personal calendar events** — parse natural-language Slack commands ("add gym tomorrow at 7 AM"), check for conflicts, request user approval, and create events in Google Calendar.
2. **Coordinate meetings between two users** — one user asks their agent to schedule with another user; the two agents negotiate via a **deterministic state-machine** (Agent-to-Agent coordination), find overlapping availability, propose a time, get dual approval, and create events in both calendars.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The coordination logic is **fully deterministic** — no LLM is used for scheduling decisions. LLM (via Groq) is only a **fallback** for intent parsing when rule-based parsing fails.

