## External Service Connections

Configured via [.env](file:///e:/CoAgent4U/.env.example):

| Service | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| **NeonDB (PostgreSQL)** | Primary data store — users, agents, coordinations, approvals, audit logs |
| **Slack** | User interaction channel — commands, approvals, notifications |
| **Google Calendar** | Read/write calendar events, check availability (FreeBusy API) |
| **Groq** | Cloud LLM for fallback intent parsing and schedule summarization |

---

## Key Architectural Principles

1. **Hexagonal Architecture** — domain logic is isolated from infrastructure via ports (interfaces) and adapters (implementations)
2. **Agent Sovereignty** — only the agent-module can access `CalendarPort`; the coordination-module talks to agents through capability ports, never directly to external APIs
3. **Deterministic Coordination** — the A2A state machine is fully deterministic; no LLM/AI influences scheduling decisions
4. **Human-in-the-Loop (HITL)** — every calendar mutation requires explicit user approval
5. **GDPR by Design** — user deletion cascades all data; audit logs track agent actions
6. **Interface-First Development** — port interfaces are defined before implementations

